This paper is primarily focused on the security and privacy of the Tor anonymity network, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also involves network measurements and path inference techniques, which are related to network infrastructure (cs.NI) and systems and control (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper discusses the impact of prediction errors on Tor security, which is related to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and cryptography (cs.CY).
